mates suggest that\nthese populations contribute ~50% of the flux from sources with 0.5 < f_850 < 5\nmJy, which is where the peak of energy is produced. We have therefore uncovered\none of the most important populations of galaxies contributing to the sub-mm\nbackground.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Sep 2005 20:08:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
